laboratory_examinations.findings: Appendix is enlarged, measuring 10 mm with trace surrounding fat stranding and fascial thickening. Oral contrast does not fill the appendix. Polypoid thickening noted at the appendiceal origin bulging into the cecum. The appendix measured approximately 6 mm on an earlier unspecified date. No gross or diffuse or focal abnormality in liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenals, and kidneys. No nephrolithiasis or hydronephrosis. No free air or free fluid.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Appendix measured approximately 6 mm on an earlier unspecified date and is enlarged to 10 mm in the current examination.
